    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "If we're viewing falling as a special `shift`, I don't think it should expand the frame because `shift` wouldn't.  But I wonder if we should make it explicit that it's different from a normal shift in that it's value-dependent, not merely index-dependent, and call it `valid_to_head` or `valid_to_tail` or `notnull_to_head` or `notnull_to_tail`.\n\n[Aside: I don't care much about the behaviour of the `df.shift(3, method='somename')` case because when I need this, I only ever need the non-nan values pushed to one of the edges.]\n"
  },
